Offered By
Greg Sharpe 4
1 AMEND House Committee Substitute for House Bill No. 2003, Page 20, Section 3.2015, Line 5
2 by inserting immediately thereafter the following:
3
4 "Section 3.2025. To the Department of Higher Education and Workforce Development and
5 public institutions of higher education
6 In reference to Sections 3.405, 3.410, 3.415, 3.420, 3.425, 3.430, 3.435, 3.440, 3.445, 3.450, and
7 3.455 of Part 1 of this act:
8 Flexibility between said sections shall exist in such amount as is necessary to prevent the
9 appropriation for any four year public institution from falling below eighty-five percent (85%),
10 or exceeding one hundred fifteen percent (115%), of its fiscal year 2026 appropriation, as
11 authorized under the provisions of House Bill 3, an Act of the 103rd General Assembly, First
12 Regular Session. When exercising flexibility, any amount flexed out from a section shall be
13 divided amongst the other sections in a pro rata fashion based on the total amount of funds
14 appropriated among all said sections. When exercising flexibility, any amount flexed into a
15 section shall be debited from the other sections in a pro rata fashion based on the total amount of
16 funds appropriated among all said sections.";
17
18 Further amend said bill by adjusting section and bill totals and intersectional references
19 accordingly.
